              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Single-image sponsored content achieves the broadest reach and is best for awareness. LinkedIn Lead Gen Forms generate the most form completions because they pre-fill user data from their profile. Video ads achieve the highest engagement rates. The best format depends on your campaign objective — match format to funnel stage.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Is LinkedIn Ads worth it for small businesses?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Only if your target buyer is a professional definable by job title or industry. With a minimum budget of $10/day, small businesses should start narrowly — targeting one specific job title in one geography — and test before scaling. LinkedIn Ads is not cost-effective for B2C audiences or impulse purchases.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How is LinkedIn Ads different from Google Ads?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Google Ads targets by search intent — people actively searching for a solution. LinkedIn Ads targets by professional profile — reaching people who fit your ideal customer profile whether or not they are searching. LinkedIn is better for early-stage pipeline building; Google is better for capturing demand that already exists. Most B2B programmes use both.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is a good LinkedIn Ads conversion rate?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>LinkedIn Lead Gen Forms typically achieve 10-13% conversion rates, significantly higher than driving traffic to a landing page (2-5%). A well-optimised LinkedIn campaign with a compelling offer and tight audience targeting can achieve 15-20% form conversion rates. Benchmark your campaigns against these ranges to diagnose underperformance.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

